<subSubSection id="C34E6527FF582E9F64FFFC84D136CE3D" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BEB36ACFF582E9F64FFFC84D136CE3D" blockId="180.[151,1437,829,1610]" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">
<emphasis id="B920EABEFF582E9F64FFFC84D35EC961" bold="true" box="[151,273,829,854]" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Carapace dorsoventrally flattened, marginal carina present, eyelobe present, pseudorostral lobes short, blunt. Antennule flagella well developed, accessory flagellum at least 0.5 length of main flagellum. Mandible unknown. Maxillule palp unknown. Pereopod 1 slender. Pereopod 5 shorter than pereopod 4 basis. Telson short, 0.5 length of uropod peduncles. Uropod endopod of 3 articles. Uropod exopod article 1 0.2 length of article 2, or less. 
<emphasis id="B920EABEFF582E9F64A7FC74D36BC9D1" box="[207,292,973,998]" italics="true" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">Female</emphasis>
with fully developed exopod on pereopod 2, rudimentary exopods on pereopods 3–4. 
<emphasis id="B920EABEFF582E9F6082FC74D76CC9D1" box="[1258,1315,973,998]" italics="true" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">
<collectingRegion id="4990F84EFF582E9F6082FC74D76CC9D1" box="[1258,1315,973,998]" country="Maldives" name="Maale" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">Male</collectingRegion>
</emphasis>
with short but non-clasping antenna, without penial lobes, without pleopods.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34E6527FF582E9F64AFFBACD0B7CE65" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BEB36ACFF582E9F64AFFBACD0B7CE65" blockId="180.[151,1437,829,1610]" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">
<emphasis id="B920EABEFF582E9F64AFFBACD309CE19" bold="true" box="[199,326,1045,1070]" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">Etymology</emphasis>
. The new genus is named 
<taxonomicName id="4C544D2FFF582E9F66EBFBAFD096CE1A" authorityName="Gerken" authorityYear="2018" box="[643,729,1046,1069]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Reyssia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B920EABEFF582E9F66EBFBAFD096CE1A" box="[643,729,1046,1069]" italics="true" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">Reyssia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in honor of Daniel Reyss, who originally described the 
<typeStatus id="54EF880EFF582E9F6104FBAFD7D3CE19" box="[1388,1436,1046,1070]" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">type</typeStatus>
species (as 
<taxonomicName id="4C544D2FFF582E9F657EFB80D053CE65" authorityName="Reyss" authorityYear="1978" box="[278,540,1081,1106]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Platytyphlops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lathierae">
<emphasis id="B920EABEFF582E9F657EFB80D053CE65" box="[278,540,1081,1106]" italics="true" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">Platytyphlops lathierae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Gender feminine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34E6527FF582E9F64AFFBE4D15BCE41" box="[199,788,1117,1142]" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" type="type_taxon">
<paragraph id="8BEB36ACFF582E9F64AFFBE4D15BCE41" blockId="180.[151,1437,829,1610]" box="[199,788,1117,1142]" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">
<emphasis id="B920EABEFF582E9F64AFFBE4D314CE41" bold="true" box="[199,347,1117,1142]" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">
<typeStatus id="54EF880EFF582E9F64AFFBE4D34DCE41" box="[199,258,1117,1142]" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">Type</typeStatus>
species
</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C544D2FFF582E9F6501FBE4D15FCE41" authority="Reyss, 1978 b" authorityName="Reyss" authorityYear="1978" box="[361,784,1117,1142]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Platytyphlops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lathierae">
<emphasis id="B920EABEFF582E9F6501FBE4D020CE41" box="[361,623,1117,1142]" italics="true" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">Platytyphlops lathierae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC54B5DFF582E9F661EFBE7D15FCE41" author="Reyss, D." box="[630,784,1117,1142]" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" pagination="71 - 84" refId="ref129474" refString="Reyss, D. (1978 b) Cumaces de profondeur de l'Atlantique tropical, Famille des Lampropidae. I. les genres Platysympus, Lamprops, Paralamprops, Platytyphlops, Pseudodiastylis, Dasylamprops et Murilamprops. Crustaceana, 35, 71 - 84. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 156854078 X 00231" type="journal article" year="1978">Reyss, 1978b</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34E6527FF582E9F64AFFB38D3EECC7D" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BEB36ACFF582E9F64AFFB38D3EECC7D" blockId="180.[151,1437,829,1610]" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">
<emphasis id="B920EABEFF582E9F64AFFB38D37BCEAD" bold="true" box="[199,308,1153,1178]" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C544D2FFF582E9F652AFB38D393CEAD" authorityName="Stebbing" authorityYear="1912" box="[322,476,1153,1178]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Platytyphlops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B920EABEFF582E9F652AFB38D393CEAD" box="[322,476,1153,1178]" italics="true" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">Platytyphlops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was erected by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC54B5DFF582E9F66FBFB38D107CEAD" author="Stebbing, T. R. R." box="[659,840,1153,1178]" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" pagination="129 - 176" refId="ref129930" refString="Stebbing, T. R. R. (1912) The Sympoda, Part 6. Annals of the South African Museum, 10, 129 - 176." type="journal article" year="1912">Stebbing (1912)</bibRefCitation>
to accommodate a new species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C544D2FFF582E9F60D2FB3BD701CEAE" authorityName="Stebbing" authorityYear="1912" box="[1210,1358,1154,1177]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Platytyphlops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peringueyi">
<emphasis id="B920EABEFF582E9F60D2FB3BD701CEAE" box="[1210,1358,1154,1177]" italics="true" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">P. peringueyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, based on males without pleopods. However, Stebbing’s material only included early juvenile males. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC54B5DFF582E9F608CFB1CD7D3CE89" author="Stebbing, T. R. R." box="[1252,1436,1189,1214]" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" pagination="129 - 176" refId="ref129930" refString="Stebbing, T. R. R. (1912) The Sympoda, Part 6. Annals of the South African Museum, 10, 129 - 176." type="journal article" year="1912">Stebbing (1912)</bibRefCitation>
included 
<taxonomicName id="4C544D2FFF582E9F656AFB70D3B1CED5" authority="G.O.Sars, 1870" authorityName="Calman" authorityYear="1905" box="[258,510,1225,1250]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Platyaspis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orbicularis">
<emphasis id="B920EABEFF582E9F656AFB70D3B1CED5" box="[258,510,1225,1250]" italics="true" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">Platyaspis orbicularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName id="4C544D2FFF582E9F6640FB70D08DCED5" authorityName="Stebbing" authorityYear="1912" box="[552,706,1225,1250]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Platytyphlops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B920EABEFF582E9F6640FB70D08DCED5" box="[552,706,1225,1250]" italics="true" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">Platytyphlops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, because the description of the species by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC54B5DFF582E9F60D2FB70D72ACED5" author="Calman, W. T." box="[1210,1381,1225,1250]" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" pagination="1 - 23" refId="ref126364" refString="Calman, W. T. (1905) The Cumacea of the Siboga Expedition. Uitkomsten of Zoologisch, Botanisch, Oceanographisch en Geologisch Gebied, 36, 1 - 23." type="journal article" year="1905">Calman (1905)</bibRefCitation>
was incomplete and adult males were not known. However, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC54B5DFF582E9F6777FB54D184CF31" author="Calman, W. T." box="[799,971,1261,1286]" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" pagination="603 - 676" refId="ref126444" refString="Calman, W. T. (1912) The Crustacea of the Order Cumacea in the collection of the United States National Museum. Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 41, 603 - 676. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.41 - 1876.603" type="journal article" year="1912">Calman (1912)</bibRefCitation>
completed the description of 
<taxonomicName id="4C544D2FFF582E9F614FFB54D35CCF1D" authority="G.O.Sars, 1870" authorityName="Calman" authorityYear="1905" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Platyaspis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orbicularis">
<emphasis id="B920EABEFF582E9F614FFB54D35CCF1D" italics="true" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">Platyaspis orbicularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, including adult males with 3 pairs of pleopods, and transferred the species to 
<taxonomicName id="4C544D2FFF582E9F6093FAA8D7D3CF1D" authorityName="sensu Sars" authorityYear="1887" box="[1275,1436,1297,1322]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Paralamprops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B920EABEFF582E9F6093FAA8D7D3CF1D" box="[1275,1436,1297,1322]" italics="true" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">Paralamprops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(transferred herein to 
<taxonomicName id="4C544D2FFF582E9F65F4FA8CD079CF79" authorityName="Stebbing" authorityYear="1912" box="[412,566,1333,1358]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Platytyphlops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B920EABEFF582E9F65F4FA8CD079CF79" box="[412,566,1333,1358]" italics="true" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">Platytyphlops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC54B5DFF582E9F663BFA8FD096CF79" author="Day, J." box="[595,729,1334,1358]" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" pagination="137 - 189" refId="ref127096" refString="Day, J. (1978) South African Cumacea, Part 3: Families Lampropidae and Ceratocumatidae. Annals of the South African Museum, 76, 137 - 189." type="journal article" year="1978">Day (1978)</bibRefCitation>
described the adult male of 
<taxonomicName id="4C544D2FFF582E9F6052FA8FD69BCF7A" authorityName="Stebbing" authorityYear="1912" box="[1082,1236,1334,1357]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Platytyphlops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peringueyi">
<emphasis id="B920EABEFF582E9F6052FA8FD69BCF7A" box="[1082,1236,1334,1357]" italics="true" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">P. peringueyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with 3 pairs of pleopods, and also transferred the species to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C544D2FFF582E9F677AFAE0D1FCCF45" authorityName="sensu Sars" authorityYear="1887" box="[786,947,1369,1394]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Paralamprops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B920EABEFF582E9F677AFAE0D1FCCF45" box="[786,947,1369,1394]" italics="true" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">Paralamprops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(transferred herein to 
<taxonomicName id="4C544D2FFF582E9F60DEFAE0D71FCF45" authorityName="Stebbing" authorityYear="1912" box="[1206,1360,1369,1394]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Platytyphlops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B920EABEFF582E9F60DEFAE0D71FCF45" box="[1206,1360,1369,1394]" italics="true" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">Platytyphlops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). This effectively placed 
<taxonomicName id="4C544D2FFF582E9F6505FAC4D048CFA1" authorityName="Stebbing" authorityYear="1912" box="[365,519,1405,1430]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Platytyphlops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B920EABEFF582E9F6505FAC4D048CFA1" box="[365,519,1405,1430]" italics="true" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">Platytyphlops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in synonymy with 
<taxonomicName id="4C544D2FFF582E9F6698FAC4D1DECFA1" authorityName="sensu Sars" authorityYear="1887" box="[752,913,1405,1430]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Paralamprops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B920EABEFF582E9F6698FAC4D1DECFA1" box="[752,913,1405,1430]" italics="true" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">Paralamprops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but 
<taxonomicName id="4C544D2FFF582E9F67BAFAC4D623CFA1" authorityName="Stebbing" authorityYear="1912" box="[978,1132,1405,1430]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Platytyphlops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B920EABEFF582E9F67BAFAC4D623CFA1" box="[978,1132,1405,1430]" italics="true" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">Platytyphlops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been resurrected (see remarks for 
<taxonomicName id="4C544D2FFF582E9F6577FA18D3F6CF8D" authorityName="Stebbing" authorityYear="1912" box="[287,441,1441,1466]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Platytyphlops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B920EABEFF582E9F6577FA18D3F6CF8D" box="[287,441,1441,1466]" italics="true" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">Platytyphlops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). However, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC54B5DFF582E9F662CFA1BD0A9CF8D" author="Reyss, D." box="[580,742,1441,1466]" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" pagination="71 - 84" refId="ref129474" refString="Reyss, D. (1978 b) Cumaces de profondeur de l'Atlantique tropical, Famille des Lampropidae. I. les genres Platysympus, Lamprops, Paralamprops, Platytyphlops, Pseudodiastylis, Dasylamprops et Murilamprops. Crustaceana, 35, 71 - 84. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 156854078 X 00231" type="journal article" year="1978">Reyss (1978b)</bibRefCitation>
described a new species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C544D2FFF582E9F606FFA18D742CF8D" authorityName="Reyss" authorityYear="1978" box="[1031,1293,1441,1466]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Platytyphlops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latheriae">
<emphasis id="B920EABEFF582E9F606FFA18D742CF8D" box="[1031,1293,1441,1466]" italics="true" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">Platytyphlops latheriae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a species in which the males are without pleopods, but which cannot be accommodated in 
<taxonomicName id="4C544D2FFF582E9F6025FA7CD6A8CFE9" authorityName="Stebbing" authorityYear="1912" box="[1101,1255,1477,1502]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Platytyphlops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B920EABEFF582E9F6025FA7CD6A8CFE9" box="[1101,1255,1477,1502]" italics="true" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">Platytyphlops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as resurrected. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC54B5DFF582E9F64FFFA53D308CC35" author="Bacescu, M." box="[151,327,1514,1538]" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" pagination="2 - 30" refId="ref126247" refString="Bacescu, M. (1988) Cumacea 1 (Fam. Archaeocumatidae, Lampropidae, Bodotriidae, Leuconidae). In: Crustaceorum Catalogus. Academic Publishing, The Hague, pp. 2 - 30." type="book chapter" year="1988">Băcescu (1988)</bibRefCitation>
declared 
<emphasis id="B920EABEFF582E9F65DDFA50D1C9CC35" box="[437,902,1513,1538]" italics="true" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">
“ 
<taxonomicName id="4C544D2FFF582E9F65D5FA50D094CC35" authority="Gerken, 2018" authorityName="Gerken" authorityYear="2018" box="[445,731,1513,1538]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Platytyphlops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latheriaei" status="incertae sedis">Platytyphlops latheriaeí</taxonomicName>
” 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21357C5FF582E9F6683FA53D1C9CC35" box="[747,902,1513,1538]" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">incertae sedis</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and suggested that a new genus would need to be erected to accommodate the species. The genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C544D2FFF582E9F6769F9B7D119CC12" authorityName="Gerken" authorityYear="2018" box="[769,854,1550,1573]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Reyssia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B920EABEFF582E9F6769F9B7D119CC12" box="[769,854,1550,1573]" italics="true" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">Reyssia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is therefore erected for the species described as 
<taxonomicName id="4C544D2FFF582E9F64FFF988D3D2CC7D" authority="Reyss, 1978 b" authorityName="Reyss" authorityYear="1978" box="[151,413,1585,1610]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lampropidae" genus="Platytyphlops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cumacea" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latheriae">
<emphasis id="B920EABEFF582E9F64FFF988D2B3CC7D" box="[151,252,1585,1610]" italics="true" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">latheriae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC54B5DFF582E9F656BF98BD3D2CC7D" author="Reyss, D." box="[259,413,1585,1610]" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" pagination="71 - 84" refId="ref129474" refString="Reyss, D. (1978 b) Cumaces de profondeur de l'Atlantique tropical, Famille des Lampropidae. I. les genres Platysympus, Lamprops, Paralamprops, Platytyphlops, Pseudodiastylis, Dasylamprops et Murilamprops. Crustaceana, 35, 71 - 84. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 156854078 X 00231" type="journal article" year="1978">Reyss, 1978b</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
